'''Maximiliano Gómez Horacio''' "El Moreno" (May 5, 1943 – May 23, 1971) was the leader of the [[Maoist]] [[Movimiento Popular Dominicano]] (MPD),<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pacoredo.org/PASADAS_EDICIONES/1028/Maximiliano.html|title=Maximiliano Gómez (El Moreno)|newspaper=¡Despertar!|language=Spanish|date=2001|accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref> a militant organization opposed to the [[Joaquín Balaguer]] government and to U.S. presence in the [[Dominican Republic]]. Commended by some, repudiated by others, the controversial figure of Maximiliano Gomez is part of the political heritage of the Dominican Republic. He oriented his limited efforts during a short period of time to battle Joaquin Balaguer's regime.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://historiadominicana.com.do/temas/articulos/341-un-libro-acerca-de-la-muerte-de-maximiliano-gomez-el-moreno.html|title=Un Libro Acerca de la Muerte de Maximiliano Gómez: El Moreno|last=Paulino|first=Alejandro|publisher=Historia Dominicana|language=Spanish|date=2008-05-11|accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref> Maximiliano Gomez was killed by poison by his lover-many claim that she did so by orders of Balaguer-and in turn she was found killed and dismembered, possibly by the same people who ordered her to poison Maximiliano Gomez.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tiempocompleto.com.do/?c=134&a=4631|title=En el 37 aniversario del asesinato de Maximiliano Gómez (El Moreno)|last=Pasos Pinedo|first=Reynaldo|publisher=Tiempo Completo|language=Spanish|date=2008-05-24|accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref>

